          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>Octr 22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revrd: Is: Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">From the friendly tone<lb/> of your letter to me
                                        when I applied to you for<lb/> a situation, I have thought
                                        you might feel<lb/> satisfied to hear of my promotion since
                                        that<lb/> period, and as patience &amp; perseverance is in
                                        all<lb/> situations of life necessary it has proved
                                        essential in<lb/> my case. I have sent you a transcript of
                                        an<lb/> article appearing in our papers, which I know<lb/>
                                        you will find a space in your “Occident” for its<lb/>
                                        reception, as all other articles relative to our people<lb/>
                                        I have been appointed assistant Hazan here in
                                        con<lb/>sequence of the physical inability of our
                                        Pastor<lb/> to perform all the duties, but cannot be under
                                        any<lb/> other denomination during his life time, my
                                        congre-<lb/>gation seems to be very well satisfied, which of
                                        course<lb/> from the style they have been accustomed to, is
                                        no very<lb/> easy matter, at any rate I have <del>?</del><lb/>
                                        <del>?</del> by his tuition approached him as near<lb/> as
                                        possible in style. I regret having heard that you had<lb/>
                                        withdrawn from the scene of your labors, but I trust<lb/>
                                        ere long that you will resume those duties, which<lb/> you
                                        have for so long so zealous by performed, as a</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>faithful alborer in the vineyard of the Lord “but it<lb/> must be
                                        unsatisfactory to you to find from the<lb/> stubbornness of
                                        heart that all your persuasive elo-<lb/>quence has been of
                                        little avail, and that your uncea-<lb/>sing labors, have
                                        effected little good, knowing the<lb/> forbearance necessary
                                        in your position, but I trust<lb/> again that you will again
                                        enter the field, and see<lb/> the successful result of your
                                        Labors</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">This being favored by a <persName>Mr Jacob<lb/>
                                                  DaCosta</persName> one of our Congregants, I have
                                        very little time<lb/> to spare but I shall continue to
                                        correspond should it<lb/> be congenial the following is an
                                        extract from the<lb/> “County Union” to which if you feel
                                        inclined you can' make any Editorial Remarks.</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">Jewish Intelligence</p>
                              <p>Our Jewish readers will feel some interest in learning<lb/> of the
                                        movements of our co-religionists in the metropolis.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">the <persName>reverend Isaac Lopez</persName>, a
                                        gentleman<lb/> who has held the appointment of Minister of
                                        the congre-<lb/>gation of the Spanish &amp; Portuguese
                                                  <del>Jews</del> Synagogue<lb/> upwards of 45
                                        years, has, from indisposition natural<lb/> to advanced age,
                                        he come incapacitated to perform<lb/> the whole of their
                                        duties belonging to his office, which,<lb/> during the
                                        period named, have been faithfully performed<lb/> by him.
                                        The congregation have therefore acted wisely<lb/> in
                                        selecting an efficient assistant in the person of the<lb/>
                                        <persName role="author">Revrd Abm H. DeLevante</persName>,
                                        who, we learn <del>enl</del> from</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>the “Standard” entered upon his duties on <date>Saturday</date>
                                        last.<lb/> we join our contemporary in sincerely wishing
                                        the<lb/> Revrd. Gentleman every happiness in his new
                                        calling<lb/> enjoying as he does, the confidence and good
                                        will of<lb/> the congregation—”County union</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">In conclusion I beg to offer my<lb/> sincere
                                        regard to you hoping you may enjoy all<lb/> the happiness
                                        attending an earthly life and the<lb/> peace of a blissful
                                        abode in a hereafter</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <persName role="author">A DeLevante</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>address <persName role="author">Revrd A. DL</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Hebrew National Institution</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <addressee>Revrd Is: Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>371 Walnut Street</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>5 doors below 13th</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Kindly favored</p>
                              <p>by <persName>J P D. R Dalorta Esq</persName></p>
